defaultBiography of Submission Authordefault, Gary Sullivan OBEdefault&#xa0;
defaultCareer Summarydefault&#xa0;
defaultGary specialises in Construction Logistics, supply chain development and regeneration.  He has over 20 years 
defaultof 
defaultexperience in the planning and operation of the logistics of 
defaultcomplex infrastructure projects. Gary has been involved with many high profile projects with BAA, AWE, BBC, MOD and the Olympics.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn addition to developing the UK’s foremost security and logistics contractor, from a standing start, to recognised industry 
defaultleader, Gary has served in the Parachute Regiment and worked for the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees. He was commissioned into the Engineer and Logistics Staff Corps in 2011.
default&#xa0;
defaultGary was awarded an OBE in Queen’s Birthday Honours List in June 2
default012 for Service to Regeneration of the Thames Gateway, and in October 2012 he received an Honorary Doctorate from Anglia Ruskin University in Business Administration.  He is a published author and a UNICEF Global Guardian.
